      "name": "Webhook",
      "webhookId": "portainer",
      "notes": "Portainer \u2014 Docker container management. Use for listing containers, starting/stopping/restarting containers, viewing logs, and managing stacks.\n\nActions:\n  containers \u2014 list all Docker containers with status. Use for \"list containers\", \"what containers are running\", \"show docker containers\".\n  start \u2014 start a stopped container. Use for \"start container\", \"bring up container\".\n  stop \u2014 stop a running container. Use for \"stop container\", \"shut down container\".\n  restart \u2014 restart a container. Use for \"restart container\", \"reboot container\".\n  logs \u2014 view recent container logs. Use for \"show logs\", \"container logs\", \"what happened in container\".\n  stacks \u2014 list all Docker Compose stacks. Use for \"list stacks\", \"show stacks\", \"what stacks are deployed\".\n  prune_images \u2014 remove unused Docker images to free disk space. Use for \"clean up images\", \"prune unused images\", \"free up docker space\".\n\nRules:\n- container name or ID is required for start, stop, restart, and logs actions.\n- logs accepts an optional tail parameter (default 50) to limit the number of lines returned.\n\n---schema\n{\n  \"action\": {\n    \"type\": \"string\",\n    \"description\": \"One of: containers, start, stop, restart, logs, stacks, prune_images\",\n    \"required\": true\n  },\n  \"container\": {\n    \"type\": \"string\",\n    \"description\": \"Container name or ID. Required for: start, stop, restart, logs\"\n  },\n  \"tail\": {\n    \"type\": \"integer\",\n    \"description\": \"Number of log lines to return. Default 50. For: logs\"\n  }\n}",
      "id": "portainer-wbhk-0001-0000-000000000001"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "let data;\nconst input = $input.item.json;\n\nif (typeof input.body === 'string') {\n  data = JSON.parse(input.body);\n} else if (typeof input.body === 'object') {\n  data = input.body;\n} else {\n  data = input;\n}\n\nconst action = (data.action || '').toLowerCase().trim();\n\nif (!action) {\n  return [{ json: { error: true, message: 'Action is required. Use one of: containers, start, stop, restart, logs, stacks.' } }];\n}\n\nconst validActions = ['containers', 'start', 'stop', 'restart', 'logs', 'stacks', 'prune_images'];\nif (!validActions.includes(action)) {\n  return [{ json: { error: true, message: `Unknown action: ${action}. Use one of: containers, start, stop, restart, logs, stacks, prune_images.` } }];\n}\n\n// Require container name for start/stop/restart/logs\nif (['start', 'stop', 'restart', 'logs'].includes(action) && !data.container) {\n  return [{ json: { error: true, message: `Container name or ID is required for ${action}.` } }];\n}\n\nconst container = (data.container || '').trim();\nconst tail = parseInt(data.tail) || 50;\n\nreturn [{ json: { action, container, tail } }];"
      },
